<item>
            <title>[MNG-985] plugin goals referenced in build/pluginManagment unexpectedly executed during lifecycle</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-985</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Goals referenced in &amp;lt;build&amp;gt;&amp;lt;pluginManagement&amp;gt; plugins are executed during the lifecycle - this is unexpected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See the attached pom.xml as an example.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running &quot;m2 install&quot; on this pom causes the &quot;war&quot; plugin to execute the &quot;war&quot; goal during the packaging phase of the lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that the goal should not execute because it is inside the &amp;lt;pluginManagement&amp;gt; section.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>WinXP SP2, Java 1.4.2_06, Maven 2.0-beta-1</environment>
